The PC application is very good. 4. I like that one can place notes without cluttering up the main mindmap. Also, I can place notes in the middle of a 'linking' connector--that is really nice. 5. Additionally could it sync to OneDrive? I have also discovered that as I only have a Tab2 which only updates to Android  4.2 it cannot support save as a pdf. That feature only arrived in KitKat 4.4. Not an issue for Simplemind but Samsung's upgrade policy. UPDATE: Many thanks for your quick response and highlighting the 'Local' function . Latest update defaults to saving & syncing to Dropbox. This now works perrfectly and so I would give Simplemind 5 Stars.

There are three things that would make the app even better, for me:  1) A grid that things could snap to. I like the fluidity of putting stuff anywhere, but for some maps I would love a little bit more structure without having to go to a strict horizontal or vertical layout.  2) Some way to cause more than the first 3 levels of a mind map to automatically continue changing colors.  3) The ability to turn on child nodes moving whenever their parents are moved as a default.

If the following issues are addressed my rating would probably go up a star or two:  1) Not certain why linking to a document isn't allowed. This isn't the iPhone. The file system is accessible. Should be able to link to any file and open it with any desired app, or fix the app. How great this would be, if you could use a mind map to organize visually arbitrary relationships between any arbitrary data on your android in a manner that is important to you. 1b) Links to URL that will open in a browser. 1c) Links to movies. 1d) Have nodes with links that just open apps. 2) Everything in this version is either a numbered list, or everything is freeform. There is no differentiation for subparts. Real world concepts, on the other hand, have some subparts ordered and some freeform. 3) Should be multiple ways to format a subtree, not just one arbitrary way. e.g. justifications, staggered, freeform flowing, etc. 4) Should be able to move a whole subtree as a unit. 5) Ideally, there should be an export format that handles crosslinked relationships.  With these things this tool becomes useful for organizing thinking. Without them it is just a prettified outline editor.

When I got the Nexus, was looking to switch my mind mapping from paper to the tablet and discovered SimpleMind. Delighted with its simplicity which masks quite a lot of capability. Together with Swype beta (still has bugs on Jelly Bean), have almost replaced my colored pens and paper. Am a long time user of Mind Manager on the desktop, and prefer this gem over Mindjet's free Android offering (went backwards with mandatory sign in to their Connect, and no offline mode). Also, developer very responsive when contacted over issue with exporting to Freemind.

My only issue so far is sluggish behavior when many nodes are showing at once (20+). The program is still workable and the best mind map interface I've come across so far. I do wish it was simpler to store the maps via Google drive though. The dropbox only shared implementation is annoying.
This is the easiest interface for mind mapping I've seen with a tablet mind mapping tool. Key when you use these tools to capture ideas and thoughts on the go.
Very easy to use but also easy on the eyes. Excellent way to quickly visualize structures, processes, workflows, etc. Well done!
Does what it says. LOVE IT!
Easy to use.  Nice display.  simple, just what I needed.
Took me ages to find this as a replacement for Thinking Space. Works well and good to have a desktop version too
Love it....helps me "see" things without having to constantly track paper.
It simply does everything I want. I especially like that the app doesn't lock me into some online service. Works great on my nexus7.

Free version works well ands easy to use but didn't work when upgraded. Contacted support they where quick to reply with suggestion but still haven't got it working consistently.issue may be with play store but that doesn't help me.
This is my first mind map program but it' extremely easy and intuitive. Exceeded my expectations.
This app help me brainstorming the idea
Best app for mind mapping on the move... Keep making it better. Cheers, Craig
Finally, a decent replacement for Mindjet which has been dysfunctional since change of ownership. Desktop version tops as well.
Exceedingly strong. Need to perfect opening from dropbox but otherwise very very strong product.

My previous review for this app was not good, for though I really, really liked the app's UI and fuctionality, moving maps from the desktop version to here was often impossible.   That has all changed with this update; it is now VERY easy to transfer mind maps back and forth through DropBox. I NOW HIGHLY RECOMMEND both this app and the desktop version... the UI is awesome. Absolutely worth the cost of upgrading now, and don't forget to buy the desktop version if you use midmapping regularly; the overall cost is MUCH more reasonable than Mindjet and its desktop version.
Best mind mapping app I've used. Can't fault it really.

Great little app but there are a few things that I find frustrating. On the xperia s the text on the nodes is offset so it shows up on the side. Also while you can leave a note on the node there is no way to show that there is a note and easily display it that I can see. Over all great and ill be using it for work but 5 stars when the offset and a way to have notes displayed is added.
Cannot export files created by free version to this paid version :(  UI is quite good. Easy to use. But still cannot beat ThinkingSpace

Very good app. I have a problem, text of a topic is not visible inside/centered of a cell but instead it is moved to the right side overlaying cell's border Update: Latest update fixed all my issues and improved this app significantly. Good work
Easy to switch between the many great options. Really like it!

It needs integrated cloud support, like Dropbox, which would make it easier to sync my maps between my phone and my tablet, but the "share" feature is nice. Also, a way of changing the shape of the individual nodes without changing the over style of the entire map would be nice, but the lack of this feature is really minor. I would have given 4.5 stars, due to no Dropbox support, if I could have, but I gave this app the benefit of the doubt because this is the best mind map tool I've used on Android.
Easy and intuitive. Would be even better with PDF option for sharing.
Zooming and editing is fast and intuitive. Color schemes are very nice. Totally worth buying.
Great job
